        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Centralized version identifier for the Dedoc package, consumed by setup.py and runtime version checks. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Package versioning, semantic version declaration. \par \b Input\/ \:  None (hardcoded version string). \par \b Output\/ \:  A single <computeroutput>__version__</computeroutput> string accessible via <computeroutput><ref refid="namespacededoc_1_1version_1a5dc678a536891bbad415bb6983ccb495" kindref="member">dedoc.version.__version__</ref></computeroutput>. \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput>__version__</computeroutput> is always a non-None string (empty string indicates development/unreleased build). \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why a separate <ref refid="version_8py" kindref="compound">version.py</ref> file? A: Single source of truth for version avoids duplication across setup.py, docs, and runtime introspection. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Added SEMANTIC TEMPLATE markup] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
<para>DATA 10[Package version string] =&gt; <bold>version</bold> \par \b Use Cases\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>[<bold>version</bold>]: BuildSystem =&gt; ReadPackageVersion =&gt; ReleaseTagging </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
